ron]] (SOS) and [[711th Special Operations Squadron|711th SOS]])</center>\nFile:USAF Combat Controller Flash.jpg|<center>[[United States Air Force Combat Control Team|Combat Controller]]</center>\nFile:USAF Combat Rescue Officer Flash.png|<center>[[Combat rescue officer|Combat Rescue Officer]]</center>\nFile:USAF Pararescue Flash.jpg|<center>[[Pararescueman]]</center>\nFile:USAF Security Forces beret flash.jpg|<center>[[United States Air Force Security Forces|Security Forces]]</center>\nFile:USAF Security Forces flash-Officer.png|<center>Security Forces Officer</center>\nFile:USAF Special Reconnaissance Flash.png|<center>[[United States Air Force Special Reconnaissance|Special Reconnaissance]]</center>\nFile:USAF Special Tactics Officer Flash.png|<center>[[United States Air Force Special Tactics Officer|Special Tactics Officer]]</center>\nFile:USAF SERE Flash.jpg|<center>[[Survival, Evasion, Resistance and Escape]] Instructor</center>\nFile:USAF Tactical Air Control Party Beret Flash.svg|<center>[[United States Air Force Tactical Air Control Party|Tactical Air Control Party]]</center>\n</gallery>\n\n==See also==\n* [[Obsolete badges of the United States military]]\n* [[Badges of the United States Air Force]]\n* [[Uniforms of the United States Air Force]]\n* [[Uniforms of the United States Navy]]\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n{{US Army uniforms}}\n{{US Army navbox}}\n{{US Air Force navbox}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:United States Military Beret Flash}}\n[[Category:Heraldry of the United States Army]]\n", "name_user": "McChizzle", "label": "safe", "comment": "\u2192\u200eUS Army:Updated 172nd's info", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/United_States_military_beret_flash"}
{"title_page": "James Moroney", "text_new": "{{short description|American rower}}\n{{Use mdy dates|date=March 2020}}\n{{Infobox sportsperson\n| name           = James Moroney\n| full_name      = \n| image          = \n| caption        = \n| nationality    = American\n| sport          = [[rowing (sport)|Rowing]]\n| birth_date     = {{birth date and age|1953|3|19}}\n| birth_place    = [[Philadelphia]], Pennsylvania, United States\n| death_date     = \n| death_place    = \n}}\n\n'''James Moroney''' (born March 19, 1953) is an American [[rowing (sport)|rower]]. He competed at the [[1972 Summer Olympics]] and the [[1976 Summer Olympics]].<ref name=\"SportsRef\">{{cite Sports-Reference |url=https://www.sports-reference.com/olympics/athletes/mo/jim-moroney-1.html |title=James Moroney Olympic Results |accessdate=August 20, 2018}}</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n{{Authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Moroney, James}}\n[[Category:1953 births]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:American male rowers]]\n[[Category:Olympic rowers of the United States]]\n[[Category:Rowers at the 1972 Summer Olympics]]\n[[Category:Rowers at the 1976 Summer Olympics]]\n[[Category:Sportspeople from Philadelphia]]\n[[Category:Pan American Games medalists in rowing]]\n\n\n{{US-rowing-bio-stub}}\n", "text_old": "{{short description|American rower}}\n{{Use mdy dates|date=March 2020}}\n{{Infobox sportsperson\n| name           = James Moroney\n| full_name      = \n| image          = \n| caption        = \n| nationality    = American\n| sport          = [[rowing (sport)|Rowing]]\n| birth_date     = {{birth date and age|1953|3|19}}\n| birth_place    = [[Philadelphia]], Pennsylvania, United States\n| death_date     = \n| death_place    = \n}}\n\n'''James Moroney''' (born March 19, 1953) is an American [[rowing (sport)|rower]]. He competed at the [[1972 Summer Olympics]] and the [[1976 Summer Olympics]].<ref name=\"SportsRef\">{{cite Sports-Reference |url=https://www.sports-reference.com/olympics