ory - Billboard|website=billboard.com}}</ref>\n! scope=\"col\" style=\"width:2.5em;font-size:90%;\"| [[Heatseekers Albums|US Heat]]<br /><ref name=\"billboard.com5\">{{cite web|url=https://www.billboard.com/music/waterparks/chart-history/TLN|title=Waterparks - Chart history - Billboard|website=billboard.com}}</ref>\n|-\n!scope=\"row\"|''[[Double Dare (album)|Double Dare]]''\n|\n* Released: November 4, 2016<ref>{{cite web|last1=Carter|first1=Emily|title=Waterparks Announce Debut Album, Stream New Single|url=http://www.kerrang.com/45084/waterparks-announce-debut-album-stream-new-single/|website=[[Kerrang!]]|publisher=[[Bauer Media Group]]|accessdate=August 31, 2016|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160831201031/http://www.kerrang.com/45084/waterparks-announce-debut-album-stream-new-single/|archivedate=August 31, 2016|date=August 31, 2016}}</ref>\n* Label: Equal Vision\n* Format: [[Compact Disc|CD]], [[Music download|DL]], [[LP Record|LP]]\n| \u2014 \n| 50\n| \u2014\n| 33\n| 10\n|-\n!scope=\"row\"|''[[Entertainment (Waterparks album)|Entertainment]]''\n|\n* Released: January 26, 2018<ref>{{cite web |last1=Rogers |first1=Jack |title=Waterparks Have Announced Their New Album |url=https://www.rocksound.tv/news/read/waterparks-have-announced-their-new-album/ |website=[[Rock Sound]] |publisher= Patrick Napier |accessdate=October 20, 2017|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20171020145955/https://www.rocksound.tv/news/read/waterparks-have-announced-their-new-album/ |archivedate=October 20, 2017 |date=October 20, 2017}}</ref>\n* Label: Equal Vision\n* Format: CD, DL, LP\n| 98\n| 13\n| 7\n| 5\n| \u2014\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| ''[[Fandom (album)|Fandom]]''\n|\n* Released: October 11, 2019<ref>{{cite web|url=https://music.apple.com/us/album/fandom/1474425377|title=FANDOM by Waterparks|website=[[Apple Music]]|accessdate=September 5, 2019}}</ref>\n* Label: [[Hopeless Records|Hopeless]]\n* Format: CD, DL, LP\n| 32<br /><ref>{{cite tweet|user=billboardcharts|number=1186304183768629249|title=Debuts on this week's #Billboard200 (1/3)|date=October 21, 2019|accessdate=October 22, 2019}}</ref>\n| 5\n| 2\n| 2\n| \u2014\n|}\n\n===Extended plays===\n{| class=\"wikitable plainrowheaders\" style=\"text-align:center;\"\n|+ List of extended plays\n! scope=\"col\"| Title\n! scope=\"col\"| Details\n! scope=\"col\" colspan=\"1\" | Peak Chart Positions  \nUS Heat<br /><ref name=\"billboard.com5\">{{cite web|url=https://www.billboard.com/music/waterparks/chart-history/TLN|title=Waterparks - Chart history - Billboard|website=billboard.com}}</ref>\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| ''Airplane Conversations''<ref name=\"Billboard Good Charlotte 2015\" />\n|\n* Released: April 3, 2012\n* Label: Self-released\n* Format: CD, DL\n| \u2014\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| ''Black Light''<ref name=\"Billboard Good Charlotte 2015\">{{cite web|last1=Payne|first1=Chris|title=Good Charlotte Proteges Waterparks Premiere Dog-Filled 'Crave' Video|url=http://www.billboard.com/articles/columns/rock/6754146/waterparks-crave-video-premiere-good-charlotte-madden-brothers-dogs|website=[[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]]|accessdate=March 10, 2016|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160310013424/http://www.billboard.com/articles/columns/rock/6754146/waterparks-crave-video-premiere-good-charlotte-madden-brothers-dogs|archivedate=March 10, 2016|date=November 9, 2015}}</ref>\n|\n* Released: June 5, 2014\n* Label: Self-released\n* Format: CD, DL\n| \u2014\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| ''Cluster''<ref>{{cite web|last1=Hines|first1=Hannah|title=Album Review: Waterparks \u2013 Cluster|url=http://idobi.com/review/album-review-waterparks-cluster/|publisher=[[idobi Radio]]|accessdate=March 10, 2016|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160214122716/http://idobi.com/review/album-review-waterparks-cluster/|archivedate=February 14, 2016|date=January 29, 2016}}</ref>\n|\n* Released: January 15, 2016\n* Label: Equal Vision\n* Format: CD, DL\n| 18\n|}\n\n===Demo albums===\n{| class=\"wikitable plainrowheaders\" style=\"text-align:center;\"\n|+ List of demo albums\n!scope=\"row\"|''1 (A Collection of Unreleased Home Demos, This is Not G, or Even an Album, Shut Up Enjoy)''\n|\n* Released: January 22, 2020\n* Label: Self-released\n* Format: Streaming\n|}\n\n===Singles===\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|-\n! Year !! Title !! Album\n|-\n| rowspan=\"3\" | 2011 || \"I Was Hiding Under Your Porch Because I Love You\" || rowspan=\"3\" | ''Airplane Conversations (EP)''\n|-\n| \"Silver\"\n|-\n| \"Fantastic\"\n|-\n| rowspan=\"2\" | 2013 || \"New Wave\"<ref>{{cite web|title=New Single - Single by Waterparks on iTunes|url=https://itunes.apple.com/us/album/new-wave-single/id676255803|publisher=[[iTunes Store]]|accessdate=June 30, 2016}}</ref> || rowspan=\"2\" | ''Black Light (EP)''\n|-\n| \"I'm a Natural Blue\"\n|-\n| 2015 || \"Crave\" || rowspan=\"1\" | ''Cluster (EP)''\n|-\n| rowspan=\"3\" | 2016 || \"Stupid For You\" || rowspan=\"4\" | ''Double Dare''\n|-\n|\"Hawaii (Stay Awake)\"<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://twitter.com/waterparks/status/781962725387677696?lang=en|title=WATERPARKS on Twitter|accessdate=October 2, 2016}}</ref>\n|-\n|\"Royal\"\n|-\n| rowspan=\"4\" | 2017 || \"Gloom Boys\"<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://newnoisemagazine.com/waterparks-premieres-gloom-boys-music-video/|title=Waterparks Premieres \"Gloom Boys\" Music Video|date=July 12, 2017|work=New Noise Magazine|accessdate=July 18, 2017|language=en-US}}</ref>\n|-\n|\"Blonde\" || rowspan=\"3\" | ''Entertainment''\n|-\n|\"Lucky People\"\n|-\n|\"Not Warriors\"\n|-\n| rowspan=\"7\" |2019\n|\"Beating Heart Baby\"<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.rocksound.tv/news/read/listen-to-waterparks-jazzy-cover-of-beating-heart-baby-by-head-automatica|title=LISTEN TO WATERPARKS\u2019 JAZZ COVER OF \u2018BEATING HEART BABY\u2019 BY HEAD AUTOMATICA, RECORDED FOR ROCK SOUND|last=Jamieson|first=Brii|date=March 15, 2019|website=Rock Sound|archive-url=|archive-date=|accessdate=June 2, 2019}}</ref>\n|''Rock Sound: Worship and Tributes Volume II''\n|-\n|\"Turbulent\"<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.rocksound.tv/news/read/waterparks-have-signed-to-hopeless-records-dropped-a-brand-new-single-turbu|title=WATERPARKS HAVE SIGNED TO HOPELESS RECORDS + DROPPED A BRAND NEW SINGLE \u2018TURBULENT\u2019|last=Jamieson|first=Brii|date=May 23, 2019|website=Rock Sound|archive-url=|archive-date=|accessdate=June 2, 2019}}</ref>\n|rowspan=\"6\"|''Fandom''\n|-\n|\"Watch What Happens Next\"<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.deadpress.co.uk/news-waterparks-debut-video-for-watch-what-happens-next |url-status=live |title=NEWS: Waterparks debut video for \u2018Watch What Happens Next\u2019! |accessdate=March 18, 2020}}</ref>\n|-\n|\"Dream Boy\"<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.kerrang.com/the-news/waterparks-have-just-released-another-new-single-dream-boy |url-status=live |title=WATERPARKS HAVE JUST RELEASED ANOTHER NEW SINGLE, DREAM BOY |accessdate=March 18, 2020}}</ref>\n|-\n|\"[Reboot]\"\n|-\n|\"High Definition\"\n|-\n|\"Easy to Hate\"\n|-\n|}\n\n==Awards and nominations==\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n!Year\n!Award\n!Category\n!Nominated Work\n!Result\n!Ref.\n|-\n|2017\n|Alternative Press Music Awards\n|Song of the Year\n|Stupid for You\n| {{nom}}\n|\n|-\n|2017\n|Alternative Press Music Awards\n|Album of the Year\n|Double Dare\n| {{nom}}\n|\n|-\n|2017\n|Alternative Press Music Awards\n|Best Breakthrough Artist\n|Waterparks\n| {{won}}\n|<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.altpress.com/news/entry/waterparks_breakthrough_artist_2017_apmas|title=Waterparks win Best Breakthrough Artist at the 2017 APMAs - News - Alternative Press|website=Alternative Press|language=en|accessdate=July 18, 2017}}</ref>\n|-\n|2017\n|The Rock Sound Awards\n|Best International Breakthrough Artist\n|Waterparks\n| {{won}}\n|\n|-\n|2019\n|The Rock Sound Awards\n|Song of the Year\n|Turbulent\n|  {{won}}\n|\n|}\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist|colwidth=30em}}\n\n{{Authority control}}\n\n[[Category:American pop punk groups]]\n[[Category:American musical trios]]\n[[Category:Musical groups from Houston]]\n[[Category:Musical groups established in 2011]]\n[[Category:Equal Vision Records artists]]\n[[Category:2011 establishments in Texas]]\n", "text_old": "{{For|the similarly named CCM group that is also from Houston|Watermark (band)}}\n{{Use mdy dates|date=May 2018}}\n{{Infobox musical artist\n| name                = Waterparks \n| background          = group_or_band\n| image               = WATERPARKS performing at Warped Tour in Hartford, CT in 2016 - DZUBAY.png\n| landscape           =  \n| caption             = Waterparks performing on [[Warped Tour]] in [[Hartford, Connecticut]] in 2016. From left to right: Awsten Knight, Otto Wood, and Geoff Wigington. \n| origin              = [[Houston|Houston, Texas]], U.S.\n| genre               = {{flatlist|<!-- These genres are sourced in the musical style section -->\n* [[Pop punk]]\n* [[pop rock]]\n* [[electropop]]\n}}\n| years_active        = 2011\u2013present<ref name=\"Alternative Press Things You Should Know Article\">{{cite web|last1=Stokes|first1=Alyson|title=5 Things You Should Know About Waterparks Before They Get Big|url=http://www.altpress.com/features/entry/5_things_you_should_know_about_waterparks|website=Alternative Press|accessdate=March 10, 2016|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160210092357/http://www.altpress.com/features/entry/5_things_you_should_know_about_waterparks |archivedate=February 10, 2016|date=February 9, 2016}}</ref>\n| label               = {{flatlist|\n* [[Hopeless Records|Hopeless]]<ref name=\"Hopeless Records signing article\">{{cite web|title=NEWS: Waterparks sign with Hopeless Records; share new song, \u2018Turbulent\u2019!|url=http://www.deadpress.co.uk/news-waterparks-sign-with-hopeless-records-share-new-song-turbulent/|website=Deadpress!|accessdate=May 23, 2018|date=May 23, 2019}}</ref>\n* [[Equal Vision Records|Equal Vision]]<ref name=\"Equal Vision signing article\">{{cite web|title=Waterparks Signs to Equal Vision Records; Debut Single \"Crave\" Out Now|url=http://www.equalvision.com/news/waterparks-signs-to-equal-vision-records-debut-single-crave-out-now/|publisher=Equal Vision Records|accessdate=March 10, 2016|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160310010432/http://www.equalvision.com/news/waterparks-signs-to-equal-vision-records-debut-single-crave-out-now/|archivedate=March 10, 2016|date=November 6, 2016}}</ref>\n}}\n| associated_acts               =  \n| website             = {{URL|waterparksband.com}}\n| current_members     = <!-- Do not change the members without a source or discussion. Undiscussed and unsourced changes and or vandalism will be reverted quickly.-->\n* Awsten Knight\n* Geoff Wigington\n* Otto Wood \n| past_members     =\n* Gage Matthieu \n* Owen Marvin \n}}\n\n'''Waterparks''' is an American [[pop rock]] band formed in [[Houston|Houston, Texas]] in 2011.<ref name=\"Houston Chronicle 2015 Article\">{{cite web|last1=Guerra|first1=Joey|title=Houston Band Waterparks is Making a Splash|url=http://www.houstonchronicle.com/entertainment/music/article/A-new-Houston-band-on-the-radar-6641114.php|website=[[Houston Chronicle]]|accessdate=March 10, 2016|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160310011112/http://www.houstonchronicle.com/entertainment/music/article/A-new-Houston-band-on-the-radar-6641114.php|archivedate=March 10, 2016|date=November 18, 2015}}</ref> The group currently consists of lead vocalist and rhythm guitarist [[Awsten Knight]], backing vocalist and lead guitarist [[Geoff Wigington]], and backing vocalist and drummer Otto Wood.<ref name=\"Houston Chronicle 2015 Article\" /><!-- Do not change the members without a source or discussion. Undiscussed and unsourced changes and or vandalism will be reverted quickly.-->\n\nThe band has released three EPs, two of which were released independently while the third was released via [[Equal Vision Records|Equal Vision]]. The group released its first full-length album, ''[[Double Dare (album)|Double Dare]]'', on November 4, 2016 via Equal Vision, then later their second album ''[[Entertainment (Waterparks album)|Entertainment]]'' under the same label on January 26, 2018.<ref>{{cite web|last1=Dickman|first1=Maggie|title=Waterparks announce debut album, drop new song\u2014listen|url=http://www.altpress.com/news/entry/waterparks_announce_debut_album_drop_new_songlisten|website=[[Alternative Press (music magazine)|Alternative Press]]|accessdate=August 31, 2016|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160831165808/http://www.altpress.com/news/entry/waterparks_announce_debut_album_drop_new_songlisten|archivedate=August 31, 2016|date=August 31, 2016}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|last1=Al-Sharif|first1=Rabab|title=Pop Punks Waterparks to Release Debut Full-Length Later This Year|url=http://www.altpress.com/news/entry/pop_punks_waterparks_to_release_debut_full_length_later_this_year|website=Alternative Press|accessdate=June 6, 2016|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160606200439/http://www.altpress.com/news/entry/pop_punks_waterparks_to_release_debut_full_length_later_this_year|archivedate=June 6, 2016|date=June 6, 2016}}</ref> On May 23, 2019, the band announced that they had left Equal Vision and was now signed on with [[Hopeless Records|Hopeless]]. Their third full-length album, entitled ''[[Fandom (album)|Fandom]]'', was released on October 11, 2019.\n\n==History==\n\nThe band was formed in 2011 by Awsten Knight and Gage Matthieu, who met while playing in different bands.<ref name=\"Houston Chronicle 2015 Article\" /><ref>{{cite web|title=Waterparks|url=http://www.altpress.com/apr/artist/september_2012_ap_290/24813/|website=Alternative Press|accessdate=March 10, 2016 |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20121014115944/http://altpress.com/apr/artist/september_2012_ap_290/24813/|archivedate=October 14, 2012|date=September 2012}}</ref> The group's first show was on August 17, 2012 at [[Warehouse Live]] in Houston<ref name=\"April 2016 Alternative Press Print Article\" /> alongside [[Invent, Animate]], DWHB, and Life as Lions.<ref>{{cite web|title=Waterparks with DWHB, Invent Animate, Life As Lions - Event Information|url=https://www.facebook.com/events/453488674682138/|via=Facebook|publisher=[[Warehouse Live]]|accessdate=March 24, 2016|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160324042027/https://www.facebook.com/events/453488674682138/|archivedate=March 24, 2016}}</ref> Their first EP, ''Airplane Conversations'', was released independently on April 3, 2012. The band continued performing at local venues throughout Texas over the following years.<ref name=\"Houston Chronicle 2015 Article\" /> The band performed as a supporting act for pop musician [[Aaron Carter]], opening his Houston [[After Party Tour|tour]] date on May 11, 2013.<ref name=\"Houston Chronicle 2015 Article\" /><ref name=\"Alternative Press '5 Crucial Facts'\">{{cite web |last1=Whitt|first1=Cassie|title=5 Crucial Factsis to Get to Know Waterparks |url=http://www.altpress.com/aptv/video/5_crucial_facts_to_get_to_know_waterparks|website=Alternative Press|accessdate=March 10, 2016 |date=March 10, 2016}}</ref> Their second EP, ''Black Light'', was released on June 5, 2014. The band also performed on the Houston dates of the [[Warped Tour]] in 2013<ref>{{cite web|title=Waterparks Photo on Facebook|url=https://www.facebook.com/Waterparks/photos/a.349830358415291.80752.175146525883676/547132505351741/?type=3&theater|publisher=[[Facebook]]|accessdate=April 2, 2016|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160402190618/https://www.facebook.com/Waterparks/photos/a.349830358415291.80752.175146525883676/547132505351741/?type=3&theater|archivedate=April 2, 2016|date=July 30, 2013}}</ref> and 2015.<ref name=\"MTV Madden Brothers 2015 Article\">{{cite web|last1=Norton|first1=Jessica|title=Don't Tell 5SOS, But the Madden Brothers Have a New Fave Band|url=http://www.mtv.com/news/2422805/waterparks-madden-bros/|publisher=MTV|accessdate=March 10, 2016|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160310021658/http://www.mtv.com/news/2422805/waterparks-madden-bros/|archivedate=March 10, 2016|date=November 9, 2015}}</ref>\n\nOn November 6, 2015, the band signed with label [[Equal Vision Records]].<ref name=\"Equal Vision signing article\" /> After searching for producers, the band chose twins [[Benji Madden]] and [[Joel Madden]] of [[Good Charlotte]] as their managers.<ref>{{cite web|last1=Patneaude|first1=Victoria|title=Singing Story: Waterparks|url=http://www.musicconnection.com/signing-story-waterparks/|website=[[Music Connection]]|accessdate=March 10, 2016|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160310023655/http://www.musicconnection.com/signing-story-waterparks/|archivedate=March 10, 2016|date=February 18, 2016}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|last1=Sherman|first1=Maria|title=Good Charlotte's Second Act: Inside Madden Brothers' Pop-Punk Reawakening|url=https://www.rollingstone.com/music/news/good-charlottes-second-act-inside-madden-brothers-pop-punk-reawakening-20151210|website=Rolling Stone|accessdate=March 10, 2016|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20151215024133/http://www.rollingstone.com/music/news/good-charlottes-second-act-inside-madden-brothers-pop-punk-reawakening-20151210?page=4|archivedate=December 15, 2015|date=December 10, 2015}}</ref> On January 15, 2016, the group released an EP titled ''Cluster'', co-produced by Benji Madden.<ref>{{cite web|last1=Stam|first1=Janneke|title=Waterparks Have Announced A Show |url=http://www.rocksound.tv/news/read/waterparks-have-announced-a-show|website=[[Rock Sound]]|accessdate=March 15, 2016 |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160315211605/http://www.rocksound.tv/news/read/waterparks-have-announced-a-show|archivedate=March 15, 2016 |date=March 15, 2016}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|last1=Chatterjee|first1=Kika|title=Listen: Waterparks (Equal Vision Records) premiere Benji Madden-produced EP|url=http://www.altpress.com/news/entry/listen_waterparks_equal_vision_records_premiere_benji_madden_produced_ep|website=Alternative Press |accessdate=March 10, 2016 |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160310022355/http://www.altpress.com/news/entry/listen_waterparks_equal_vision_records_premiere_benji_madden_produced_ep |archivedate=March 10, 2016|date=January 17, 2016}}</ref> [[Mikey Way]] known as the bassist of [[My Chemical Romance]] played bass for the EP. On November 19, 2015, the band performed with Good Charlotte during the group's comeback performance at [[Troubadour (West Hollywood, California)|The Troubadour]] in [[West Hollywood, California]].<ref name=\"'Crave' single & video article\">{{cite web|last1=Witherow|first1=Barbara|title=Waterparks Signs to Equal Vision, Releases New Music Video Full of Puppies|url=http://substreammagazine.com/2015/11/equal-vision-records-signs-waterparks-releases-new-music-video-full-of-puppies/|website=[[Substream Magazine]]|accessdate=March 10, 2016|date=November 10, 2016}}</ref>\n\nThe group performed on the Black Cat Tour supporting [[Never Shout Never]] in 2016,<ref>{{cite web|last1=Merchant|first1=Anam|title=Never Shout Never and Metro Station breeze through Chicago|url=http://substreammagazine.com/2016/02/never-shout-never-chicago-il-2516/|website=[[Substream Magazine]]|accessdate=April 30, 2016|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160228154945/http://substreammagazine.com/2016/02/never-shout-never-chicago-il-2516/|archivedate=February 28, 2016|date=February 9, 2016}}</ref> and on every date of the 2016 [[Warped Tour]].<ref>{{cite web|last1=Sharp|first1=Tyler|title=Next round of bands announced for Warped Tour 2016|url=http://www.altpress.com/news/entry/next_round_of_bands_announced_for_warped_tour_2016|website=Alternative Press|accessdate=March 22, 2016|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160322235619/http://www.altpress.com/news/entry/next_round_of_bands_announced_for_warped_tour_2016 |archivedate=March 22, 2016|date=March 22, 2016}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|last1=Biddulph|first1=Andy|title=See The FULL Vans Warped Tour Line-Up|url=http://www.rocksound.tv/news/read/heres-the-line-up-for-this-summers-vans-warped-tour|website=[[Rock Sound]]|accessdate=March 22, 2016|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160322235807/http://www.rocksound.tv/news/read/heres-the-line-up-for-this-summers-vans-warped-tour|archivedate=March 22, 2016|date=March 22, 2016}}</ref> The band then embarked on the End The Madness Tour supporting [[Sleeping with Sirens]] in late 2016.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.upsetmagazine.com/read/sleeping-sirens-state-champs-tonight-alive-waterparks-us-tour/|title=Sleeping With Sirens, State Champs, Tonight Alive and Waterparks for US tour|last1=Taylor|first1=Sam|date=August 16, 2016|website=Up Set Magazine|publisher=The Bunker Publishing|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160816123547/http://www.upsetmagazine.com/read/sleeping-sirens-state-champs-tonight-alive-waterparks-us-tour/|archivedate=August 16, 2016|accessdate=August 16, 2016}}</ref>\n\nThe group released a single titled \"Stupid For You\" on August 31, 2016 in promotion of its debut album, ''[[Double Dare (album)|Double Dare]].'' They later released two additional singles, \"Hawaii (Stay Awake)\", and \"Royal\", before the album's release on November 4, 2016.<ref>{{cite web|last1=Biddulph|first1=Andy|title=Waterparks Announce Debut Album, Release Huge Summer Song|url=http://www.rocksound.tv/news/read/waterparks-announce-debut-album-release-huge-summer-song|website=[[Rock Sound]]|accessdate=August 31, 2016|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160831165902/http://www.rocksound.tv/news/read/waterparks-announce-debut-album-release-huge-summer-song|archivedate=August 31, 2016|date=August 31, 2016}}</ref>\n\nIn March 2017, the group joined fellow bands [[SWMRS]] and The Wrecks as supporting acts on [[All Time Low]]'s tour of the [[United Kingdom]] and [[Ireland]]. Later, during the Summer of 2017, the groups reunited for All Time Low's Young Renegades Tour, this time touring the United States. [[Night Riots]] performed in place of SWMRS on the tour's Dallas and Houston dates.\n\nOn October 20, 2017, the band announced their second studio album, ''[[Entertainment (Waterparks album)|Entertainment]]'', with a release date of January 26, 2018. Alongside ''Entertainment''<nowiki/>'s announcement, the band released the album's first single, \"Blonde\".<ref>{{cite web|last1=Dickman|first1=Maggie|title=Waterparks release catchy new song \"Blonde\" from forthcoming album, 'Entertainment'|url=https://www.altpress.com/news/entry/waterparks_new_song_blonde_new_album_entertainment|website=Alternative Press|publisher=Alternative Press|accessdate=October 20, 2017}}</ref> Pre-orders for the new album became available on November 2, 2017. On December 13, 2017, the band released the second single from the album, titled \"Lucky People\". On January 17, 2018, Waterparks released the third and final single from ''Entertainment'', titled \"Not Warriors\". The album was released on January 26, 2018 via Equal Vision. ''Entertainment'' peaked at No. 98 on the [[Billboard 200|''Billboard'' 200]] chart on February 10, 2018.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.billboard.com/music/waterparks/chart-history/billboard-200/song/1064400|title=Waterparks Entertainment Chart History|work=Billboard|accessdate=March 29, 2018}}</ref>\n\nOn May 23, 2019, the band released their first single off of their upcoming album, \"Turbulent\" and announced that they got signed to [[Hopeless Records]].<ref name=\"Hopeless Records signing article\"/><ref>{{cite web|title=Waterparks Reveal \u201cTurbulent\u201d Release Date, Single Art Sparks Theories|url=https://www.altpress.com/news/waterparks-turbulent-release-date/|website=Alternative Press|accessdate=May 23, 2018|date=May 23, 2019}}</ref> On August 12, 2019, the band released the second single, \"Watch What Happens Next\", along with a music video and the announcement of the album to be released on October 11, 2019.<ref>{{cite web|first=Whitney|last=Shoemaker|url=https://www.altpress.com/news/waterparks-fandom-album-watch-what-happens-next/|title=Waterparks Reveal 'Fandom' date with \u201cWatch What Happens Next\u201d video|website=[[Alternative Press (magazine)|Alternative Press]]|date=August 12, 2019|accessdate=August 12, 2019}}</ref> On August 16, 2019, the band released their third single, \"Dream Boy,\" along with a music video.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.altpress.com/news/waterparks-dream-boy-awsten-knight-meaning/|title=Waterparks reveal \u201cDream Boy\u201d is About Pressure of \u201cFan Expectations\u201d|date=August 12, 2019|accessdate=October 14, 2019}}</ref> On September 12, 2019, the fourth single, \"[Reboot]\" was released.<ref>{{cite web|title=Waterparks further prove Awsten Knight isn't a \"Dream Boy\" in \"[Reboot]\"|url=https://www.altpress.com/news/waterparks-reboot-new-song-fandom-awsten-knight/|website=Alternative Press|accessdate=October 15, 2019|date=September 12, 2019}}</ref> On September 25, 2019, they released their fifth single for the album, \"High Definition,\" along with a music video.<ref>{{cite web|title=Waterparks Reveal \u201cTurbulent\u201d Release Date, Single Art Sparks Theories|url=https://www.altpress.com/news/waterparks-high-definition-awsten-knight-fandom/|website=Alternative Press|accessdate=October 15, 2019|date=September 25, 2019}}</ref> On October 17, 2019, \"Easy to Hate\" was released as the sixth single, along with a music video.<ref>{{cite web|title=Waterparks Release 'Easy To Hate' Music Video|url=https://www.broadwayworld.com/bwwmusic/article/Waterparks-Release-Easy-To-Hate-Music-Video-20191017|accessdate=October 17, 2019|date=October 17, 2019}}</ref>\n\nOn January 22, 2020, frontman Awsten Knight tweeted that if he got 20,000 retweets he would release a new Waterparks album that day. The tweet did get 20,000 retweets within a few hours, and on [[SoundCloud]] Knight self-released ''1 (A Collection of Unreleased Home Demos, This is Not G, or Even an Album, Shut Up Enjoy)'', a demo album that consists of unreleased Waterparks demos, including songs Knight has teased on his Instagram such as \"Lemonade\", \"Noise\", and \"Glitter Times\".\n\n==Musical style and influences==\nDrawing from a diverse pool of stylistic influences, the band is primarily characterized as [[pop punk]],<ref name=\"AMP\">{{cite web|title=Amped Featured Album of the Week:Waterparks/Fandom|url=https://www.ampeddistribution.com/2019/10/amped-featured-album-of-the-week-waterparks-fandom|accessdate=October 20, 2019}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.theyoungfolks.com/music/91772/album-review-waterparks-double-dare/|title=Album Review: Waterparks \u2013 \"Double Dare\"|publisher=theyoungfolks}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.allmusic.com/artist/waterparks-mn0003460365|title=Waterparks|publisher=}}</ref><ref name=\"Alternative Press Mad Article\">{{cite web|last1=Al-Sharif|first1=Rabab|title=Get an Exclusive First Listen of Waterparks' 'Mad All the Time'|url=http://www.altpress.com/features/entry/waterparks_premiere_new_song_mad_all_the_time|website=[[Alternative Press (music magazine)|Alternative Press]]|accessdate=March 10, 2016|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160119191702/http://www.altpress.com/features/entry/waterparks_premiere_new_song_mad_all_the_time|archivedate=January 19, 2016|date=December 17, 2016}}</ref> [[pop rock]]<ref>{{cite web|last1=Biddulph|first1=Andy|title=Waterparks - 'Double Dare'|url=http://www.rocksound.tv/reviews/read/waterparks-double-dare}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=Album Review: 'Fandom' by Waterparks|url=https://thesoundboardreviews.com/2019/10/14/album-review-fandom-by-waterparks/|website=The Sound Board Reviews|accessdate=October 14, 2019}}</ref> [[Pop music|pop]],<ref>{{cite web|title=Waterparks \u2013 Fandom (Album Review)|url=https://wallofsoundau.com/2019/10/10/waterparks-fandom-album-review/|accessdate=October 14, 2019}}</ref> [[electropop]]<ref>{{cite web|title=Onk OK Rock @ Showbox SoDo \u2013 Seattle, WA|url=https://musicwhynot.com/one-ok-rock-showbox-sodo-seattle-wa/|accessdate=October 20, 2019}}</ref> and [[alternative rock]],<ref name=\"AMP\"/> but also incorporates elements of [[hip hop]], [[Electronic music|electronic]], [[Indie rock|indie]], [[Punk rock|punk]], and [[jazz]] music.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.bringthenoise.com/artist/waterparks|title=I'm watching Waterparks on Bring the Noise.|website=the NOISE|accessdate=January 30, 2018}}</ref> Frontman Awsten has stated that he considers the group to be a rock band that has garnered significant inspiration from pop music.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.upsetmagazine.com/features/waterparks-oh-man-weve-learned-nothing/|title=Waterparks: \"Oh man, we've learned nothing!\"|date=November 14, 2016|work=Upset|accessdate=January 30, 2018|language=en-US}}</ref> Since the departure of former bassist Gage Matthieu, the band has remained without a bass player in its official lineup, instead performing with a rotation of fill-in bass players or using pre-recorded backing tracks in live appearances. They have cited [[Sum 41]], [[Blink-182]], [[Good Charlotte]], [[Kesha]], [[My Chemical Romance]], [[Green Day]],<ref name=\"April 2016 Alternative Press Print Article\">{{cite journal|title=What's My Scene Again?|journal=[[Alternative Press (music magazine)|Alternative Press]]|date=April 2016|volume=30|issue=333|page=80}}</ref> [[Fall Out Boy]], [[Linkin Park]], and [[Saves the Day]]<ref>{{cite web|last1=Monger|first1=James Christopher|title=Waterparks {{!}} Biography & History|url=http://www.allmusic.com/artist/waterparks-mn0003460365/biography|publisher=[[AllMusic]]|accessdate=May 26, 2016|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160526022341/http://www.allmusic.com/artist/waterparks-mn0003460365/biography|archivedate=May 26, 2016}}</ref> as musical influences.\n\n==Band members==\n\n'''Current members''' <!-- Do not change the members without a source or discussion. Undiscussed and unsourced changes and or vandalism will be reverted quickly.-->\n* Awsten Knight \u2013 lead vocals, rhythm guitar <small>(2011\u2013present)</small>\n* Geoff Wigington \u2013 lead guitar, backing vocals  <small>(2011\u2013present)</small>\n* Otto Wood \u2013 drums, backing vocals <small>(2012\u2013present)</small>\n  \n'''Former members'''\n* Gage Matthieu \u2013 bass <small>(2011\u20132012)</small><ref name=\"Billboard Good Charlotte 2015\" />\n* Owen Marvin \u2013 drums <small>(2011\u20132012)</small>\n'''Touring members'''\n* [[Mikey Way]] \u2013 bass <small>(2016, 2018)</small><ref>{{cite web|first=Beth|last=Casteel|url=https://www.altpress.com/news/mikey-way-to-join-waterparks-on-vans-warped-tour/|title=Mikey Way Join Waterparks on Vans Warped Tour|publisher=Alternative Press|date=June 15, 2018|accessdate=July 21, 2018}}</ref>\n\n===Timeline===\n\n==Discography==\n===Studio albums===\n{| class=\"wikitable plainrowheaders\" style=\"text-align:center;\"\n|+ List of studio albums\n! scope=\"col\" rowspan=\"2\"| Title\n! scope=\"col\" rowspan=\"2\"| Details\n! scope=\"col\" colspan=\"5\"| Peak chart positions\n|-\n! scope=\"col\" style=\"width:2.5em;font-size:90%;\"| [[Billboard 200|US]]<br /><ref name=\"billboard.com1\">{{cite web|url=https://www.billboard.com/music/waterparks/chart-history/TLP|title=Waterparks - Chart history - Billboard|website=billboard.com}}</ref>\n! scope=\"col\" style=\"width:2.5em;font-size:90%;\"| [[Top Rock Albums|US Rock]]<br /><ref name=\"billboard.com2\">{{cite web|url=https://www.billboard.com/music/waterparks/chart-history/RCK|title=Waterparks - Chart history - Billboard|website=billboard.com}}</ref>\n! scope=\"col\" style=\"width:2.5em;font-size:90%;\"| [[Alternative Albums|US Alt.]]<br /><ref name=\"billboard.com3\">{{cite web|url=https://www.billboard.com/music/waterparks/chart-history/ALT|title=Waterparks - Chart history - Billboard|website=billboard.com}}</ref>\n! scope=\"col\" style=\"width:2.5em;font-size:90%;\"| [[Independent Albums|US Indie]]<br /><ref name=\"billboard.com4\">{{cite web|url=https://www.billboard.com